  {layer_group_id: nil, name: "Mangroves", slug: "mdg_mangroves", layer_type: "layer", zindex: nil, active: false, order: nil, color: nil, info: "{\"description\":\"According to FAO (2007), fishermen travel different distances into the ocean along the eastern and western coasts of the country (due to variable distances from the shore to the continental shelf). Therefore different distances from the coast were used: mangroves and coral reefs falling within a 30-km zone in the Mozambique Channel off the west coast of Madagascar, and a five-km zone of the Indian Ocean off the east coast were included. \", \"source\":\"Conservation International. 2015. Monitoring Natural Capital and Human Well-being in Madagascar: A National Demonstration of Indicators for Sustainable Development. Page 62. ISBN 978-1-934151-92-1. Conservation International, Arlington, VA. Available from http://www.metricsci.org/assets/metrics-technical-report-madagascar-2015.pdf.</p><p>FAO (Jol Nageon de Lestang). 2007. Study on Safety at Sea for Small-scale Fisheries: Southwest Indian Ocean.<p><p>Giri, C.P., Ochieng, E., Tieszen, L.L., Zhu, Z., Singh, A., Loveland, T.R., Masek, J., and Duke, N., 2011, Status and distribution of mangrove forests of the world using earth observation satellite data: Global Ecology and Biogeography, v. 20, no. 1, p. 154-159.</p></p>\", \"link\":\"http://www.metricsci.org/assets/metrics-technical-report-madagascar-2015.pdf. </p>\", \"link\":\"http://www.conservation.org/projects/Pages/metrics.asp\" }", layer_provider: "cartodb", css: "#mangroves_MDG[zoom >= 7]{polygon-opacity: 0.0; line-color: #1a6d33; line-width: 0.9; line-opacity: 1;}\r\n#mangroves_MDG[zoom < 7]{marker-opacity: 0.2; marker-line-color: #1a6d33; marker-line-width: 0.9; marker-line-opacity: 1;}", interactivity: "", opacity: 1.0, query: "SELECT * FROM mangroves_MDG", locate_layer: true, icon_class: nil, published: true, legend: "{\"type\": \"custom\", \"data\": [ { \"name\":\"Mangroves\", \"value\" : \"#1a6d33\"}]}", zoom_max: 100, zoom_min: 0, dashboard_order: nil, download: false, dataset_shortname: "Conservation International. 2015. Monitoring Natural Capital and Human Well-being in Madagascar: A National Demonstration of Indicators for Sustainable Development. Page 62. ISBN 978-1-934151-92-1. Conservation International, Arlington, VA. Available from http://www.metricsci.org/assets/metrics-technical-report-madagascar-2015.pdf. <p>FAO (Jol Nageon de Lestang). 2007. Study on Safety at Sea for Small-scale Fisheries: Southwest Indian Ocean.<p><p>Giri, C.P., Ochieng, E., Tieszen, L.L., Zhu, Z., Singh, A., Loveland, T.R., Masek, J., and Duke, N., 2011, Status and distribution of mangrove forests of the world using earth observation satellite data: Global Ecology and Biogeography, v. 20, no. 1, p. 154-159.  ", dataset_source_url: "http://www.metricsci.org/assets/metrics-technical-report-madagascar-2015.pdf. ", title: "Mangroves", start_date: nil, end_date: nil, spatial_resolution: "", spatial_resolution_units: "", temporal_resolution: "", temporal_resolution_units: "", data_units: "", update_frequency: "", version: "", processing: "", description: "According to FAO (2007), fishermen travel different distances into the ocean along the eastern and western coasts of the country (due to variable distances from the shore to the continental shelf). Therefore different distances from the coast were used"},
