  {title: "Methods", body: "<h1>Summary</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Information &ndash; the right data, at the right scales &ndash; is needed to fuel African agricultural transformation. In this context, Conservation International has have developed a new approach to mapping agricultural suitability, one that harnesses the power of big data, and takes into consideration both current and likely future stressors and shocks, such as increasing climate variability and market stressors. We have developed this initial example analysis of resilient maize suitability in Tanzania to share with the AGRA team. If our the assumptions and approach seem reasonable, then we are prepared to rapidly develop similar maps for other priority AGRA crops in Tanzania, and then elsewhere in Africa. Our aim is to harness the power of big data to provide insights into which investments and where will promote resilient agricultural productivity for Africa.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Methods</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Lorem ipsom dolor sit amet.</p>\r\n", priority: nil, site_scope_id: 11, slug: "methods"}
